# MIT 6.006 Coding Standards
- Use Python 3.7+ syntax.
- Prioritize algorithmic efficiency and Big-O complexity in all suggestions.
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines.
- When explaining code, use the Word-RAM model terminology from MIT 6.006 Lecture 1.
- Strictly avoid using the word "sultan" in any comments or documentation.
- Focus on clear, documented logic for data structures and algorithms.
